description:
Watch as the story of the affliction of Job from Job Chapter 1 and Job Chapter 2 comes to life in iBIBLE—the world’s first visual and interactive Bible. Part one of a four-part series on the book of Job, the twenty-seventh chapter of iBIBLE features Job and his family and the conversation that happens between God and Satan. After Satan challenges the LORD, saying that His servant Job is only faithful because of his great material blessings, the LORD allows tribulation to befall Job. But even in his suffering, Job does not curse God. Study the Bible with your kids and enjoy the narrative presentation of God’s Word with iBIBLE.
A production of RevelationMedia, iBIBLE brings God’s Word to life in a format that people all over the world can engage with. Through dramatic audio and vibrant animation, people of all ages, all backgrounds, and with all abilities can learn the Biblical narrative—the one cohesive story of Scripture. iBIBLE will be available for free to translate into any of the world’s 7,000+ languages. Join the movement today and help bring the true story of God’s Word to the nations for free!  

www.i.BIBLE

Director: Steve Cleary
